The rise in anti-Asian hate continues to impact youth. Do you know the legal responsibilities of public schools to address and eradicate anti-Asian bullying and harassment? Join our upcoming CLE webinar on Thursday, Feb. 3 to learn more. Register: http://bit.ly/antibullyingcle:=:https://us02web.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_hFevuMShTQSJYJROd1tYMg

We're offering a CLE webinar on Thursday, Feb. 3 that will explore the legal responsibilities of public schools to address and eradicate anti-Asian bullying and harassment. The webinar will cover the distinction between bullying and harassment, the legal elements of a harassment complaint, the tensions between protected speech and conduct requiring actions by schools, and when schools are obligated to address off campus conduct. Thank you to Amy Berman of the National Academy of Education for being our speaker for this important and timely topic. Register: bit.ly/antibullyingcle:=:https://us02web.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_hFevuMShTQSJYJROd1tYMg

Simu Liu Was Told He Didn‚Äôt Have the ‚ÄòIt Factor‚Äô to Star in ‚ÄòCrazy Rich Asians‚Äô: ‚ÄòMaybe I Was Too Desperate‚Äô "I didn't have that thing that made people want to watch it." Simu Liu desperately wanted to get ‚ÄúCrazy‚Äù before becoming a MCU superhero. The ‚ÄúKim‚Äôs Convenience‚Äù breakout star revealed that he auditioned four times for Jon M. Chu‚Äôs ‚ÄúCrazy Rich Asians‚Äù and ultimately lost out on the role. Why? Well, because Liu apparently didn‚Äôt have the ‚ÄúIt‚Äù factor for Hollywood. ‚ÄúThrough some sort of broken telephone, whether it had gone through a studio exec or a casting director before it got to our side, we got, ‚ÄòWell Simu doesn‚Äôt have the X-factor. The It factor,'‚Äù the ‚ÄúShang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings‚Äù star said during the podcast ‚ÄúHow To Fail With Elizabeth Day.‚Äù ‚ÄúAnd that was just such a crushing blow for me.‚Äù Liu continued, ‚ÄúIt felt like someone was telling me that I just wasn‚Äôt good enough, that I just wasn‚Äôt likable. I didn‚Äôt have that thing that made people want to watch it. It was at a time that was very difficult for me, I was trying to figure out whether I could be the lead character or whether I could only be a supporting character for my entire career.‚Äù The whole experience led to Liu reflecting on his approach to auditions, with the star saying, ‚ÄúIt forced me to take a step back and realize that maybe I wanted it too badly. Like maybe I was too desperate and that desperation was showing in my work. There had to be an element of confidence in what I was doing and self-assuredness. I had to trust I was talented and I was watchable and I was good.‚Äù Read more on IndieWire

4:20 PM UPDATE - The Severe T-Storm risk has been upgraded to level 3 (numerous storms) for portions of South Dakota. As for north-central North Dakota, uncertainty remains for this afternoon. Showers and storms near the international border, in Burke County, have had a difficult time intensifying, minimizing this afternoon's severe weather threat. For this evening and tonight, our focus shifts to South Dakota, far south-central North Dakota and eastern North Dakota. Thunderstorms are expected to move into the region and maintain their intensity. If the storms hold together, a few supercells will be possible and capable of producing large hail and damaging winds. -Meteorologist Henry Blakes

11:51 PM Weather Update A Severe T-Storm Watch has been issued until 6 AM CDT for portions of central and eastern North Dakota and northern South Dakota. A second round of showers and thunderstorms will impact the region tonight and Tuesday morning. Large hail, gusty winds and heavy rain will be the primary threats. -Meteorologist Henry Blakes
Rain is expanding in coverage as it gradually moves north. Precipitation is forecast to impact the far southwestern and northern counties later this afternoon and evening. -Meteorologist Henry Blakes
